# Admin Design System

Before editing any admin screen or component, align to this system.
See also: `ui-theme.mdc` (tokens), `unified-app-standards.mdc` (code rules).

**Goal:** One premium, mobile-first ISP admin product — same palette, rhythm, and components everywhere.

## Token map (never hardcode hex)

| Role | Token |
|------|-------|
| Layout constants | `@/theme/adminDesign` (`adminDesign.layout`, `adminDesign.typography`) |
| Screen canvas / list padding | `@/theme/adminScreenStyles` (`adminScreenStyles.canvas`, `.listContent`) |
| Page shell wrapper | `AdminScreenLayout` from `@/components/admin` |
| Page canvas | `adminColors.canvasBg` |
| Card / surface | `adminColors.cardBg` |
| **App header bar** | `@/theme/adminHeader` (`adminHeaderTheme`) |
| Primary accent (actions, active, selected) | `adminColors.primary` |
| Primary text | `colors.textPrimary` |
| Secondary text | `colors.textSecondary` |
| Muted / labels | `adminColors.sectionLabel` |
| Border | `colors.borderDefault` |
| Success | `adminColors.badgeActive` |
| Warning | `adminColors.badgePending` |
| Error / destructive | `adminColors.badgeBlocked` or `colors.errorRed` |
| Soft shadow | `shadow.card` from `@/theme/spacing` |

New colors → add to `@/theme/admin.ts` first. Never one-off hex in screens.

## Spacing (strict scale only)

Use `@/theme/spacing`: `xxs` 4 · `xs` 8 · `sm` 12 · `md` 16 · `lg` 20 · `xl` 24 · `xxl` 32 · `xxxl` 40.

| Use | Token |
|-----|-------|
| Page horizontal padding | `spacing.lg` (20) |
| Section gap | `spacing.md`–`spacing.lg` (16–20) |
| Card padding | `spacing.md` (16) |
| Field gap | `spacing.sm` (12) |
| Label → field | 6 (only allowed off-scale micro-gap) |
| Title → content | `spacing.sm` (12) |

No random magic numbers. Refactor off-scale screens toward this rhythm.

## Radius, cards, shadows

- Card radius: `adminDesign.radius.card` (22) or `radius.xl` (20) — one family everywhere
- Card: white bg, 1px `colors.borderDefault`, `shadow.card`, padding `spacing.md`
- No heavy shadows or harsh outlines
- KPI / summary cards: reuse `KPICard`, `SectionCard` from `@/components/admin`

## Typography (`@prime/ui` typography + admin context)

| Role | Size / weight |
|------|----------------|
| Page title | 20–22 semibold |
| Section title | 18 semibold |
| Card title | 16–18 semibold |
| Body | 14–16 regular |
| Label | 12–13 semibold, uppercase, `colors.textSecondary` |
| Helper / metadata | 12–13, muted |
| KPI number | bold, not oversized |

Same hierarchy on every screen. Readable line height on mobile.

## Buttons

Reuse `@prime/ui` `Button` or admin patterns. Target spec when extending:
- Height 48–52 · radius `radius.lg` (16) · primary fill `adminColors.primary`
- White semibold label · consistent pressed opacity
- Secondary: outlined/muted · destructive: error tokens only
- Min touch target 44pt

## Inputs & forms

Reuse `@/components/admin`: `FormField`, `SelectField`, `DateField`, `FilterChips`.
- Height 52–56 · radius `radius.lg` · label above field
- Body 16 · placeholder muted · focus: accent border
- React Hook Form + Zod · inline errors · group fields in `SectionCard`
- Long forms → stepped sections, same visual language

## Icons

- `@expo/vector-icons` (Ionicons) — one style set, consistent sizes
- No emoji as section icons on admin screens (use icon components or `SectionHeader` patterns)
- Icons support scanning, not decoration

## Layout pattern (every screen)

1. Header (stack nav or in-screen)
2. Optional summary / hero KPI block
3. Filters · actions · key status
4. Main content (list / cards / form)
5. Secondary content
6. Footer / bottom nav

One clear primary purpose per screen. Important content near top. No giant header gaps.

## Lists & dashboards

- `FlatList` / `FlashList` · stable keys · memoized rows
- Compact status chips via `StatusBadge` — color = meaning only
- Metadata quieter than titles · actions in consistent positions
- Dashboard: aligned KPI cards · reserve loud color for urgent states · charts only when they clarify

## States (required)

Loading (skeleton), error (retry), empty (explanation + next action) on every data-driven screen.

## Quality check before finishing

Does it match theme tokens, spacing rhythm, card/button/input style, typography, icons, and feel like the same ISP admin product as Dashboard, Users, Officers, HR, and Support screens?

## Shared components (prefer reuse)

`@/components/admin`: `FormField`, `SelectField`, `DateField`, `SectionCard`, `FilterChips`, `StatusBadge`, `KPICard`, `SearchBar`, `SectionHeader`
`@prime/ui`: `Screen`, `Button`, `EmptyState`, `ErrorState`
